               <interp inst="t18600507-500" type="date" value="18600507"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18600507-500-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-500-18600507 t18600507-500-offence-1 t18600507-500-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>500. <persName id="def1-500-18600507" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-500-18600507" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-500-18600507" type="age" value="32"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-500-18600507" type="surname" value="BOND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-500-18600507" type="given" value="WALTER GRIMSTONE"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WALTER GRIMSTONE BOND</hi>
                  </persName> was <hi rend="italic">again</hi> indicted<rs id="t18600507-500-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18600507-500-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18600507-500-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="fraud"></interp>for unlawfully obtaining 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. of <persName id="t18600507-name-751" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-751" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-751" type="surname" value="MITCHELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-751" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18600507-500-offence-1 t18600507-name-751"></join>James Mitchell</persName>, and 8<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. of <persName id="t18600507-name-752" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-752" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-752" type="surname" value="COLEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-752" type="given" value="CLARA"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18600507-500-offence-1 t18600507-name-752"></join>Clara Coleman</persName>, by feloni<lb></lb>ously pretending that he had the authority of <persName id="t18600507-name-753" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-753" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-753" type="surname" value="FREAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-753" type="given" value="GEORGE HENDER"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18600507-500-offence-1 t18600507-name-753"></join>George Hender Frean</persName> and another to sell certain horses.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIGH</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600507-name-754" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-754" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-754" type="surname" value="MITCHELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-754" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES MITCHELL</persName>
                  </hi>. <hi rend="italic">The evidence given by this witness in the former case was read over to him, to which he assented, and added</hi>—When the prisoner offered me the horse, I believed it was one of the horses of the firm, and that he had authority to sell it; I paid the money under that belief.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Are you the prosecutor of this indictment? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; if I do not get the horse I shall prosecute in the County Court.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. LILLEY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> When you had got the horse, did you mention it to Simpson? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and to all the men—I told them where I had bought the horse—there was no concealment in the transactions between me and the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIGH</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you ever say one word about this before, that the firm knew you had bought the horse? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I did not tell the Magis<lb></lb>trate so when I was examined before him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600507-name-755" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-755" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-755" type="surname" value="COLEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-755" type="given" value="CLARA"></interp>CLARA COLEMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. <hi rend="italic">The evidence of this witness was read over to her, to which she assented.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600507-name-756" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-756" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-756" type="surname" value="MEAD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-756" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE MEAD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am general manager to Messrs. Peek—Mr. Peek, junior, is under age, he seldom attends to the business—Mr. Frean's depart<lb></lb>meut is attending the markets, purchasing wheat and flour, and arranging with me—everything that is done by the firm comes under my knowledge and cognizance—the prisoner generally receives his orders from me, but for</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186005070227"></xptr>
               <p>some little while till the business was more thoroughly established, Mr. Peek came down and assisted us—I never gave the defendant directions, directly or indirectly, to dispose of these two horses—(<hi rend="italic">The witness's former evidence was here read over to him, to which he assented</hi>)—I received this notice on Monday morning, 23d April—he was there for an hour or two on Saturday afternoon—I went to his house the first thing on Tuesday morning, but he was not at home—I went twice that day and he was not at home—he did not come to the establishment, and I ordered him to be given in custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Supposing the prisoner wanted some clover for his horses, would not he ask Mr. Peek about it and not you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He might, because he obtained the clover from the Messrs. Peek, at Eastchot—that could be done without any communication with me, if he had arranged that the supply should come in that way—I do not remember that he has ever asked me, with respect to clover, during the whole time he has been there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did he ever ask you for beans, or anything else? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He would ask for oats aud beans because Mr. Peek bought them at the market—he never applied to me for cart grease—such things as breaking of harness were continually brought before me, before Mr. Bond came into the employ.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600507-name-757" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-757" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-757" type="surname" value="PEEK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-757" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES PEEK</persName>
                  </hi>. <hi rend="italic">The evidence of this witness was read over to him, to which he assented, and added</hi>—I was not there between the 20th and 30th March; I was in Devonshire—the last time I was there in March was about the 8th or 9th; I was there almost daily before that for one or two hours—it was about two months previously that I complimented him upon the look of the horses—I do not remember any conversation between us about the horses for a month previous to my departure for the country.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Does your memory enable you to speak with any confidence as to the last time you were there? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I can remember up to the day I left town, that was the 8th or 9th,(<hi rend="italic">Looking at a memorandum-book</hi>)—I made the memorandum at the time, it was on 9th March that I went to Devonshire, and it was about a month previous to that that I spoke to the prisoner about the condition of the horses, but I cannot say positively—I did not leave it to him to do what was right with regard to the horses—I did not order clover, straw, and corn for them—the prisoner gave me a list on two or three occasions, and I submitted it to Mr. Frean.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIGH</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you authorize the prisoner to do anything without your knowledge? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Never.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600507-name-758" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-758" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-758" type="surname" value="PEEK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-758" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD PEEK</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Junior</hi>), I am one of the firm of Peek, Frean, and Peek—the prisoner was in our employ—I never gave him authority to sell or shoot any of the horses, or deal with them in any shape or form—I never saw him before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. LILLEY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">submitted there was no case to go to the Jury, as there was no proof that Mr. George Hender Frean had not given the prisoner authority to sell the horses.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIGH</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">contended, that having called one of the partners and the manager of the firm to prove that the prisoner had no authority to sell, that the case ought to go to the Jury, especially as it appeared, by Mr. Mead's evidence, that the primmer denied selling them at all.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>The Court considered that in an indictment for false pretences in which the authority of two persons would be necessary, it was not sufficient to prove the authority of one, and therefore directed a verdict of</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18600507-500-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18600507-500-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600507-500-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="directed"></interp>NOT GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>
               </p>
            </div1>
